other_tests.findings: Initial scout image shows multiple surgical clips in the right upper quadrant. Cannulation and opacification of the distal pancreatic duct appears normal. The distal common bile duct was cannulated and the intra- and extra-hepatic biliary tree was opacified, normal in morphology, contour, and caliber, without evidence of filling defects. The remnant cystic duct is visualized without evidence of leak. A stone fragment was seen in the duodenum near the ampulla.
